The paper discusses the use of machine learning to select kernels in a case study deploying high performance SYCL kernels in libraries that target a range of heterogeneous devices from desktop GPUs to embedded accelerators. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auto-tuning and heterogeneous programming systems, which could fall under the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Architecture (cs.AR).
